<subSubSection id="6F65FDA5069FB4CECEC804E8C8E45621" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1CE6AB5474706BD9DCDB7EA3C2FD18FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Geographic distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1ABEC8D2D58CDD2DDEC128CA7BDCCFCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">
Known from the Gila River watershed in Arizona and New Mexico (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8B797FB6524BA9C887108BB68B458CDB" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Geographic distribution of B. mimbres in Arizona and New Mexico." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1007.60012.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/492374" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="C29A16FA435D4B44C3E153C9753C8329" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1007.60012.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/492374" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" start="Figure 10" startId="F10">
<paragraph id="97D3FB0BB2259B476E4A3EEEA3783501" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis id="F779FD3672067845E7972521AA0F12F8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Figure 10.</emphasis>
Geographic distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="96399D760E882A2A7FBB7950677BAE5A" family="Carabidae" genus="B." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="B. mimbres" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" rank="species" species="mimbres">
<emphasis id="8473B693DFA09FCA060D711A75D9C7CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">B. mimbres</emphasis>
